Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate a third of the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the remaining whole garlic cloves (unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it.

Roast the parcel in the oven until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the grated garlic, @breadcrumbs{10%grams}, @tomato ketchup{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British beef mince{240%grams}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands.

Shape into mini sausage shapes, 4 per person. Flatten to make koftas.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the koftas onto a large baking tray. Bake on the middle shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

In a medium bowl, combine the mashed garlic with the @mayonnaise{64%grams} and @red wine vinegar{12%ml}.

Stir in the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set your slaw aside.

Just before the koftas and chips are ready, pop the @plain taco tortillas{4.2} (2 per person) into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

To make your tacos, spoon the slaw down the centre of each tortilla. Scatter over a few of the chips, then top with the koftas.

Drizzle the @honey{2%tbsp} over the koftas and finish by scattering over the @crispy onions{1%sachet}.

Serve the remaining chips alongside.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!